---
import VizLayout from '../../layouts/VizLayout.astro';
const title = "2.2 Sorting Algorithms · GATE DA";
---
<VizLayout {title} currentPath="/module2/2-2-questions" pageCss="/assets/css/pages/1-1-questions.css">

<div class="gd-breadcrumb">
  <a href="/index.html">Home</a><span>›</span>
  <a href="/module2.html">Module 2</a><span>›</span>
  2.2 Questions
</div>
<a class="gd-pill-link" href="/module2/viz-2-2-sorting.html">← Theory &amp; Visualizations</a>

<div class="gd-viz-header">
  <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <span class="gd-badge gd-badge--subject">Module 2 · DSA</span>
    <span class="gd-badge gd-badge--pyq">10 questions · MCQ / NAT / MSQ</span>
  </div>
  <h1 id="top">2.2 Sorting Algorithms Practice Questions</h1>
  <p>GATE-style questions. Attempt before revealing answer. NAT/MSQ: no negative marking; MCQ: −⅓ mark.</p>
</div>

<div class="q-score-bar">
  <div>
    <div class="q-score-bar__count"><span id="score-num">0</span> / 10</div>
    <div class="q-score-bar__label">correct answers revealed</div>
  </div>
  <button class="q-score-bar__reset" onclick="resetAll()">Reset all</button>
</div>

<div class="q-list">

  <div class="q-card" id="qc1">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q1</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Which of these sorting algorithms is <strong>stable</strong>?</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q1-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> Quick sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> Heap sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> Merge sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> Selection sort</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(1,'mcq','C')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q1-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (C) Merge sort.</span></b> Merge, insertion and bubble preserve the relative order of equal keys. Quick, heap and selection do not.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc2">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q2</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">The worst-case time complexity of merge sort is</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q2-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $O(n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $O(n \log n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $O(n^2)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $O(\log n)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(2,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q2-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) $O(n \log n)$.</span></b> Merge sort always splits in half and merges in linear time: $T(n)=2T(n/2)+n$.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc3">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q3</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Which comparison sort runs in $O(n \log n)$ worst case using $O(1)$ auxiliary space?</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q3-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> Merge sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> Quick sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> Heap sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> Counting sort</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(3,'mcq','C')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q3-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (C) Heap sort.</span></b> Heap sort is in-place and $O(n \log n)$ worst case. Merge needs $O(n)$ space; quick is $O(n^2)$ worst; counting is not comparison-based.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc4">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q4</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Bubble sort on [5, 1, 4, 2, 8]. The number of swaps equals the number of inversions. How many swaps occur?</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q4-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">swaps</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(4,3.9,4.1)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q4-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 4.</span></b> Inversions are (5,1), (5,4), (5,2) and (4,2) = 4. Bubble sort performs one swap per inversion, so 4 swaps.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc5">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q5</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">The lower bound for any comparison-based sorting algorithm is</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q5-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $\Omega(n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $\Omega(n \log n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $\Omega(n^2)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $\Omega(\log n)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(5,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q5-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) $\Omega(n \log n)$.</span></b> The decision tree has $n!$ leaves; its height is $\Omega(\log n!) = \Omega(n \log n)$.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc6">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q6</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">The best-case time of insertion sort (already sorted input) is</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q6-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $O(n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $O(n \log n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $O(n^2)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $O(1)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(6,'mcq','A')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q6-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (A) $O(n)$.</span></b> On a sorted array each element needs one comparison and no shifts — a single linear pass.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc7">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q7</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">The auxiliary space of standard merge sort is</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q7-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="7" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $O(1)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="7" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $O(\log n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="7" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $O(n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="7" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $O(n \log n)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(7,'mcq','C')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q7-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (C) $O(n)$.</span></b> Merging requires a temporary buffer the size of the merged run, i.e. $O(n)$ extra.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc8">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q8</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Quick sort attains its worst-case $O(n^2)$ when</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q8-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> the pivot is always the median</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> the array is already sorted and the pivot is the first element</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> all elements are distinct</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> the array is reversed and pivot is random</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(8,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q8-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> A first-element pivot on a sorted array gives maximally unbalanced partitions of sizes 0 and $n-1$, yielding $O(n^2)$.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc9">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q9</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Radix sort on $n$ integers each with $d$ digits in base $b$ runs in $O(d(n+b))$. For $n=1000$ 3-digit decimal numbers ($d=3$, $b=10$), the dominant term $d \cdot n$ equals</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q9-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">value</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(9,2999,3001)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q9-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 3000.</span></b> $d \cdot n = 3 \times 1000 = 3000$ — radix sort beats comparison sorts here since $d$ is small.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc10">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q10</span><span class="q-type q-type--msq">MSQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks · no negative</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Which sorts are <strong>in-place</strong> (use $O(1)$ or $O(\log n)$ auxiliary space)? (Select all.)</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q10-opts">
      <label class="q-opt q-opt--msq"><input type="checkbox" data-q="10" data-val="A"> <span class="q-opt-key">A</span> Heap sort</label>
      <label class="q-opt q-opt--msq"><input type="checkbox" data-q="10" data-val="B"> <span class="q-opt-key">B</span> Merge sort (standard)</label>
      <label class="q-opt q-opt--msq"><input type="checkbox" data-q="10" data-val="C"> <span class="q-opt-key">C</span> Quick sort</label>
      <label class="q-opt q-opt--msq"><input type="checkbox" data-q="10" data-val="D"> <span class="q-opt-key">D</span> Insertion sort</label>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkMsq(10,['A','C','D'])">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q10-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (A), (C), (D).</span></b> Heap, quick (in-place partition, $O(\log n)$ stack) and insertion are in-place. Standard merge sort needs $O(n)$ extra and is <span class="ans-wrong">not</span> in-place.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div><!-- end q-list -->

<div style="margin-top:32px;padding-top:24px;border-top:1px solid var(--gd-border);display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
  <a class="gd-pill-link" href="/module2/2-2-bank.html" style="margin-top:0;">Question Bank (20 Qs) →</a>
  <a class="gd-pill-link" href="/module2.html" style="margin-top:0;">← Module 2 Overview</a>
</div>

<script is:inline slot="scripts">
var scores={};
function updateScore(){document.getElementById('score-num').textContent=Object.values(scores).filter(Boolean).length;}
function selectOpt(el){var q=el.dataset.q;var card=document.getElementById('qc'+q);if(card.classList.contains('q-card--correct')||card.classList.contains('q-card--wrong'))return;document.querySelectorAll('[data-q="'+q+'"].q-opt:not(.q-opt--msq)').forEach(function(o){o.classList.remove('q-opt--selected');});el.classList.add('q-opt--selected');}
function check(q,type,correct){var card=document.getElementById('qc'+q);var selected=document.querySelector('[data-q="'+q+'"].q-opt--selected');var ansEl=document.getElementById('q'+q+'-ans');var btn=card.querySelector('.q-check-btn');if(!selected)return;var val=selected.dataset.val;var isCorrect=val===correct;document.querySelectorAll('[data-q="'+q+'"].q-opt:not(.q-opt--msq)').forEach(function(o){o.classList.remove('q-opt--selected');if(o.dataset.val===correct)o.classList.add('q-opt--correct');else if(o.dataset.val===val&&!isCorrect)o.classList.add('q-opt--wrong');o.style.pointerEvents='none';});card.classList.add(isCorrect?'q-card--correct':'q-card--wrong');ansEl.style.display='block';btn.disabled=true;scores[q]=isCorrect;updateScore();}
function checkNat(q,min,max){var input=document.getElementById('q'+q+'-input');var ansEl=document.getElementById('q'+q+'-ans');var card=document.getElementById('qc'+q);var btn=card.querySelector('.q-check-btn');var val=parseFloat(input.value);var isCorrect=!isNaN(val)&&val>=min&&val<=max;input.classList.add(isCorrect?'q-nat__input--correct':'q-nat__input--wrong');input.disabled=true;ansEl.style.display='block';btn.disabled=true;card.classList.add(isCorrect?'q-card--correct':'q-card--wrong');scores[q]=isCorrect;updateScore();}
function checkMsq(q,correctArr){var card=document.getElementById('qc'+q);var ansEl=document.getElementById('q'+q+'-ans');var btn=card.querySelector('.q-check-btn');var checked=Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[data-q="'+q+'"]:checked')).map(function(c){return c.dataset.val;});var isCorrect=correctArr.length===checked.length&&correctArr.every(function(v){return checked.includes(v);});card.querySelectorAll('.q-opt--msq').forEach(function(label){var val=label.querySelector('input').dataset.val;if(correctArr.includes(val))label.classList.add('q-opt--correct');else if(checked.includes(val))label.classList.add('q-opt--wrong');label.querySelector('input').disabled=true;label.style.pointerEvents='none';});card.classList.add(isCorrect?'q-card--correct':'q-card--wrong');ansEl.style.display='block';btn.disabled=true;scores[q]=isCorrect;updateScore();}
function resetAll(){scores={};updateScore();document.querySelectorAll('.q-card').forEach(function(c){c.classList.remove('q-card--correct','q-card--wrong');});document.querySelectorAll('.q-opt:not(.q-opt--msq)').forEach(function(o){o.classList.remove('q-opt--selected','q-opt--correct','q-opt--wrong');o.style.pointerEvents='';});document.querySelectorAll('.q-nat__input').forEach(function(i){i.value='';i.disabled=false;i.classList.remove('q-nat__input--correct','q-nat__input--wrong');});document.querySelectorAll('.q-opt--msq input').forEach(function(c){c.checked=false;c.disabled=false;});document.querySelectorAll('.q-opt--msq').forEach(function(l){l.classList.remove('q-opt--correct','q-opt--wrong');l.style.pointerEvents='';});document.querySelectorAll('.q-answer').forEach(function(a){a.style.display='none';});document.querySelectorAll('.q-check-btn').forEach(function(b){b.disabled=false;});}
</script>
</VizLayout>
